  "text": "and may assume that \u03b4C 3 is decomposed on the basic covariant 3-forms, as in Eq. [CITATION_1] . Clearly, the gauge transformations \u03b4C 3 = d\u03b1 2 with \u03b1 2 = 1 2 E B \u2227 E A \u03b1 AB do not change the field strength and thus are not of any interest at the present stage. If interested in \u03b4C 3 variations which produce \u03b4H 4 in (34), we can simplify the general expression for \u03b4C 3 variation in (35) by factoring out the gauge transformations. Particularly, we can start with \u03b4C 3 of the form (17) with",
